# Core Rules

> Apply to the **entire project** (frontend and backend).
> Stack-specific rules live in `.cursor/rules/frontend/` and `.cursor/rules/backend/`.

## Rule Files

| File | Scope |
|------|-------|
| `architecture.mdc` | Architecture principles — SOLID, SRP, KISS, DRY |
| `workflow.mdc` | How to approach tasks — analysis, planning, communication |
| `code-style.mdc` | TypeScript, naming, imports |
| `engineering.mdc` | Dependencies, security, validation, performance |

## Priority

Stack-specific rules override core when they are more specific:

`frontend/*` or `backend/*` > `core/*`
